      "strengths_deep_dive": [
        "MLFA's operational strength lies in its specialized focus on the National Security Criminal Defense Center (NSCDC). In 2021 alone, the organization managed <cite id=\"11\">112 new and active legal cases</cite>, providing a critical safety net for individuals facing federal investigations. Their commitment to community education is further evidenced by reaching <cite id=\"8\">505 training attendees</cite> to increase legal literacy. Financially, the organization is resilient, maintaining <cite id=\"12\">5.3 months of working capital</cite> in working capital, which ensures stability for long-term litigation that can span several years."
      ],
      "summary": "The Muslim Legal Fund of America (MLFA) is a specialized legal defense organization dedicated to protecting the constitutional rights of Muslims in the United States. Operating at the intersection of national security and civil liberties, MLFA provides <cite id=\"1\">expert legal representation in criminal defense, civil rights, and immigration law</cite>. The organization is uniquely positioned as a <cite id=\"2\">zakat-eligible legal fund</cite>, allowing donors to fulfill religious obligations while supporting high-stakes litigation that protects the broader community. In 2022, the organization reported <cite id=\"3\">total revenue of $3,239,841</cite>, maintaining a <cite id=\"4\">93/100 overall score from Charity Navigator</cite>. Their work is characterized by a focus on systemic issues, including <cite id=\"5\">national security criminal defense and FBI interview representation</cite>. Beyond individual cases, MLFA invests in the sustainability of the Muslim nonprofit sector through <cite id=\"6\">nonprofit governance and legal counsel</cite>. Their impact is evidenced by significant legal victories, including <cite id=\"7\">high-profile terrorism case acquittals</cite> and the management of <cite id=\"8\">101 litigated or processed cases</cite> in a single year. With a <cite id=\"9\">Platinum Seal of Transparency from Candid</cite>, MLFA demonstrates a high level of accountability in its mission to ensure equal protection under the law regardless of race or religion.",
